  "story": {
    "title": "The Poet and the Coach",
    "body": "In a small local town, there lived a young poet named Arif. He loved to write scenes from daily life on every blank sheet he could find. One day, his school announced an exam on creative writing. Arif wanted to take part, but he had no control over his nervousness. His coach, Mr. Reza, gave him a direct piece of advice: write an outline before you begin, and give a clear description of each scene. Arif followed this example. He visited the local store to buy a notebook, sat down quietly, and started writing. He did not let silly thoughts distract him. He wrote about a magical forest and a creature that suffered alone until technology brought it help. He printed his story on clean sheets and mailed it to the school board. On exam day, everyone loved his novel style of writing. The coach smiled and said, 'You have no limit when you believe in yourself.' Arif never forgot those words.",
    "comprehension": [
